escrow 103 long preamble text 3   1:   LEX: «Escrow».

escrow 103 long preamble text 3   3:   Preamble: ‹This is a long preamble text delimited with 3 line breaks and the quote in the first definition line.›.


escrow 103 long preamble text 3   6:   "«Payer»" is a person.
escrow 103 long preamble text 3   7:   "«Payee»" is a person.
escrow 103 long preamble text 3   8:   "«Arbiter»" is a person.
escrow 103 long preamble text 3   9:   "«Fee»" is an amount.

escrow 103 long preamble text 3  11:   The «Payer» pays an amount into escrow, appoints the «Payee», appoints the «Arbiter», and fixes the «Fee».

escrow 103 long preamble text 3  13:   CLAUSE: «Pay Out».
escrow 103 long preamble text 3  14:   The «Arbiter» may pay from escrow the «Fee» to themselves, and afterwards pay the remainder of the escrow to the «Payee».

escrow 103 long preamble text 3  16:   CLAUSE: «Pay Back».
escrow 103 long preamble text 3  17:   The «Arbiter» may pay from escrow the «Fee» to themselves, and afterwards return the remainder of the escrow to the «Payer».


